Questions:-
1. You want to show how discount varies with price range (two continuous variables). Which visual would best show the relationship: histogram, scatter plot, line chart, or heatmap? Explain why.
2. In a table visual showing Product Name, Price, Discount, Rating, how would you apply conditional formatting so that: Discounts above 50% appear in green Discounts below 10% appear in red Ratings below 3 are highlighted in orange
3. You want to compare Average Price vs Average Rating per Subcategory. Which chart type would you use (column + line combo, scatterplot, etc.) and why? How would you interpret if expensive categories have lower ratings?
4. From the dataset, suppose you find that higher discounts don’t necessarily lead to higher ratings. How would you prove or disprove this in Power BI using measures/visualizations?
5. Assume you added a column Scraping Date. How would you create a visualization in Power BI to track average discount trend over time? Which chart type would you choose and why?
6. If your KPI card shows: Average Price = ₹950 Average Discount = 40% Average Rating = 3.8 ⭐ How would you interpret these results from a business perspective? What insights can an e-commerce manager take?
